{
  "doc_id": "17039",
  "text": "Other agents that have been proposed as treatment for MMN include cyclophosphamide [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] and azathioprine [CITATION_4] ]. According to one case report cyclophosphamide and autologous stem cell transplantation are ineffective in MMN [Axelson et al. 2008a ]. Beneficial effects have been observed in patients treated with the monoclonal anti-CD20 antibody rituximab, [CITATION_5] ; however, other groups were unable to confirm this [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] ]. More recently, a randomized controlled trial evaluated the efficacy of mycophenolate mofetil as adjunctive therapy for MMN [CITATION_8] ]. Twenty-eight patients who received IVIg were randomized to receive in addition to IVIg either mycophenolate mofetil or placebo for a period of 12 months. A reduction of the IVIg dose to 50% served as the primary endpoint.",
